<subSubSection id="C3438BE7FF54FF6B9C91C2D88C1BFE0A" lastPageId="136" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE6D86CFF54FF6B9C91C2D888A5FE32" blockId="135.[151,1437,151,2034]" lastBlockId="136.[151,1436,152,498]" lastPageId="136" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF54FF649C91C2D88853F831" bold="true" box="[198,312,1967,1993]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC8A59DFF54FF649D1CC2C78881F832" author="Quate, L. W." box="[331,490,1968,1994]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" pagination="55 - 74" refId="ref103778" refString="Quate, L. W. (1960) Diptera: Empididae. Insects of Micronesia, 13, 55 - 74." type="journal article" year="1960">Quate (1960)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF54FF649E3FC2C78B91F831" authorityName="Bezzi sensu Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[616,762,1968,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF54FF649E3FC2C78B91F831" box="[616,762,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F34E98FCFF54FF649F1EC2C78ABAF832" box="[841,977,1968,1994]" name="Micronesia" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
. His record was based on Melander's identification and he re-described this species and illustrated some structures. However, a comparison of Quate's description with the specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF5BFF6B9EF4C5EF8A5EFF49" authorityName="Bezzi sensu Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[675,821,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9EF4C5EF8A5EFF49" box="[675,821,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that we have examined, reveals some differences between them. Quate indicates (l.c.: 64) that the metanotum, hypo- and metapleuron are brown, while they are yellow (as in Bezzi's original description) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF5BFF6B9E9BC59F8A34FEF9" authorityName="Bezzi sensu Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[716,863,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9E9BC59F8A34FEF9" box="[716,863,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Also, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF5BFF6B9FB5C59F8D1DFEF9" authorityName="Bezzi sensu Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[994,1142,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9FB5C59F8D1DFEF9" box="[994,1142,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the third costal section (between veins R2+3 and R4+5) is nearly twice as long as the second section (between veins R1 and R2+3) (they are subequal according to Quate). Finally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF5BFF6B9E98C44F8A36FEA9" authorityName="Bezzi sensu Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[719,861,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9E98C44F8A36FEA9" box="[719,861,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer wing (2.0 mm vs. 
<quantity id="4CA17589FF5BFF6B9884C44F8C09FEAA" box="[1235,1378,312,338]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.7 mm</quantity>
) and a somewhat different male terminalia (at least as it could be seen 
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9FF6C4178A80FE81" box="[929,1003,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">in situ</emphasis>
). So, we believe that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC8A59DFF5BFF6B98B8C4178CF7FE82" author="Quate, L. W." box="[1263,1436,352,378]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" pagination="55 - 74" refId="ref103778" refString="Quate, L. W. (1960) Diptera: Empididae. Insects of Micronesia, 13, 55 - 74." type="journal article" year="1960">Quate's (1960)</bibRefCitation>
record of 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF5BFF6B9D5FC4FF88FEFE59" authorityName="Bezzi sensu Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[264,405,392,417]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9D5FC4FF88FEFE59" box="[264,405,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F34E98FCFF5BFF6B9D8BC4FF8B0BFE5A" box="[476,608,392,418]" name="Micronesia" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
is a misidentification and actually he re-described and illustrated a different species (see below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE6D86CFF5BFF6B9C91C4AF8C1BFE0A" blockId="136.[151,1436,152,498]" box="[198,1392,472,498]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">
The relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF5BFF6B9DEFC4AF8B2EFE09" authorityName="Bezzi sensu Quate" authorityYear="1960" box="[440,581,472,497]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosae">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9DEFC4AF8B2EFE09" box="[440,581,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">E. formosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear beyond inclusion within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFF5BFF6B9874C4AF8DAAFE09" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[1059,1217,472,497]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiata">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFF5BFF6B9874C4AF8DAAFE09" box="[1059,1217,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">E. ephippiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
